Definition 13. A constraint on a part $P$ is a map $\phi:B_{P}\to\operatorname{\textbf{Prop}}$. The type of constraints on $P$ is $\operatorname{\textbf{Prop}}^{P}$.
Definition 2.1 (Def. 1.4, [mss:operads]). A non-$\Sigma$ operad in a symmetric monoidal category $(\mathcal{C},\otimes,1)$ is a collection $(P_{r})_{r\geq 1}\subset\mathcal{C}$ together with a family of structure morphisms $\displaystyle\gamma_{r,(s_{i})}\colon P_{r}\otimes\bigotimes_{1\leq i\leq r}P_% {i}\to P_{\sum_{i}s_{i}},\qquad r,s_{1},\ldots s_{r}\geq 1$ satisfying the following axioms: (associative) The following diagram commutes: $\displaystyle\displaystyle{P_{r}\otimes\bigotimes_{1\leq i\leq r}\Bigl{(}P_{s_% {i}}\otimes\bigotimes_{1\leq j\leq s_{i}}P_{t_{ij}}\Bigr{)}}\ar[d]^{% \operatorname{id}\otimes\bigotimes_{1\leq i\leq r}\gamma_{s_{i},(t_{ij})_{j}}}$ $\displaystyle\displaystyle{P_{r}\otimes\prod_{1\leq i\leq r}P_{\sum_{j}t_{ij}}% }\ar[d]^{\gamma_{r,(\sum_{j}t_{ij})}}$ $\displaystyle\xymatrix$$\displaystyle\displaystyle{P_{r}\otimes\bigotimes_{1\leq i\leq r}\Bigl{(}P_{s_% {i}}\otimes\bigotimes_{1\leq j\leq s_{i}}P_{t_{ij}}\Bigr{)}}\ar[d]^{% \operatorname{id}\otimes\bigotimes_{1\leq i\leq r}\gamma_{s_{i},(t_{ij})_{j}}}$ Definition-Proposition 2.2. For any $r\geq 1$ and $\mathbf{s}\in\mathbb{Z}_{\geq 1}^{r}$, define $T_{r,(s_{i})}$ to be the following element of $K_{\sum_{i}s_{i}}^{\operatorname{tree}}$: Define $\gamma_{r,(s_{i})}\colon K_{r}^{\operatorname{tree}}\times\prod_{i}K_{s_{i}}^{% \operatorname{tree}}\to K_{\sum_{i}s_{i}}^{\operatorname{tree}}$ by setting $\gamma_{r,(s_{i})}\coloneqq\gamma_{T_{r,(s_{i})}}$, where the latter map was defined in Def.-Lem. 2.14, [b:2ass]. Then $(K_{r})_{r\geq 1}$ with these composition maps forms a non-$\Sigma$ operad in the category of posets. Similarly, $(\overline{\mathcal{M}}_{r})_{r}$ is a non-$\Sigma$ operad in Top. Proof. To prove that the operations $\gamma_{r,(s_{i})}\colon K_{r}^{\operatorname{tree}}\times\prod_{i}K_{s_{i}}^{% \operatorname{tree}}\to K_{\sum_{i}s_{i}}^{\operatorname{tree}}$ make $(K_{r})_{r\geq 1}$ into a non-$\Sigma$ operad, we must verify (associative) and (unit). (unit) is an immediate